The paper deals with the automatic construction of an autonomous agent's modular architecture, which is a problem that falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also combines results from two different domains, namely autonomous planning through Markov Decision Processes (cs.SY) and a general data clustering approach (cs.LG). The paper also discusses self-organizing problems, which is a topic that falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO, and cs.NE.
